docs.abstract: At least five more top managers are leaving the world’s largest sports footwear and apparel company after an investigation into complaints of harassment and bias. The departures follow six others.
docs.snippet: At least five more top managers are leaving the world’s largest sports footwear and apparel company after an investigation into complaints of harassment and bias. The departures follow six others.
docs.lead_paragraph: A sweeping investigation into workplace behavior at Nike has resulted in the departures of five more top-level executives, raising to 11 the number of senior managers to leave the company as it continues to overhaul its upper ranks amid widespread allegations of harassment and discrimination against female employees.

headline.main: 5 More Nike Executives Are Out Amid Inquiry Into Harassment Allegations
headline.print_headline: Nike Exodus Of Managers Grows to 11 After Inquiry

byline.original: By Julie Creswell and Kevin Draper

docs.abstract: The landmark settlement between Wells Fargo and the Fed shows regulators’ new emphasis on making board members responsible for their institutions’ conduct.

docs.lead_paragraph: On a Thursday evening in mid-January, a group of top Wells Fargo executives sat down for dinner in an upscale surf-and-turf restaurant near the White House. At nearby tables, power brokers ate seafood on ice and sipped cocktails out of copper mugs.

headline.main: How Wells Fargo and Federal Reserve Struck Deal to Hold Bank’s Board Accountable

docs.abstract: Without claiming a definitive link, a safety group said fatalities rose in states that legalized recreational use of cannabis. Elsewhere, they fell.
docs.snippet: Without claiming a definitive link, a safety group said fatalities rose in states that legalized recreational use of cannabis. Elsewhere, they fell.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pedestrian deaths in traffic accidents have reached levels not seen in years, and a safety group has sought to explain why. It has identified several possible causes, like digital distractions and an increase in driving. Now it has added another: marijuana.

headline.main: Where Pedestrian Deaths Are Up, Is Marijuana to Blame?
headline.print_headline: Pedestrian Deaths Rose In States Where Pot Is Legal, a Study Finds
